{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In recent advancements in KG completion tasks, leveraging sequence-to-sequence models has also shown great promise.",
    "Saxena et al. (2022) propose transforming KG link prediction into a sequence-to-sequence task and replacing the traditional triple scoring method with auto-regressive decoding.",
    "Similarly, GenKGC (Xie et al., 2022) leverages pre-trained language models to convert the KGs completion task into a sequence-to-sequence generation task.",
    "The core idea of path learning is to treat the connection paths between entities as the basis, thereby capturing both explicit information and implicit relationships in structured KGs.",
    "BERTRL (Zha et al., 2022) leverages pre-trained language models and finetunes them with relation instances and reasoning paths as training samples."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Saxena et al. (2022) propose transforming KG link prediction into a sequence-to-sequence task and replacing the traditional triple scoring method with auto-regressive decoding.",
    "BERTRL (Zha et al., 2022) leverages pre-trained language models and finetunes them with relation instances and reasoning paths as training samples."
